* Raspberry Pi History

Original objetive [[https://www.raspberrypi.org/about/][The Making of Pi]]

Concerned about the year-on-year decline in the numbers and skills levels of the A Level students applying to read Computer Science.

Home PC and games console vs. the Amigas, BBC Micros, Spectrum ZX and Commodore 64 machines. Earlier generation learned to program on.

Licensed manufacture to element 14/Premier Farnell and RS Electronics. Within two years it had sold over two million units.

